{"TopicId":217322,"ForumId":198,"TopicTitle":"Probe Cores are Very Hard to Figure out Their Orientation","CreatedByName":"Anth","CreatedById":161238,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-05-23T02:04:49Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Anth","CreatedById":161238,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-05-23T02:04:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSP2 Version: 0.1.2.0.22258\u003Cbr\u003E\nOperating System: Windows 10\u003Cbr\u003E\nCPU\u002BGPU\u002BRAM: i9 9900K\u002B3070ti\u002B32GB\u003Cbr\u003E\nMods Used: None\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EIssue:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nKSP1 I can see exactly which way the probe core is facing (with the ones I have shown below)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nKSP2 I have no idea\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EScreenshot Comparisons:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNote how easy the KSP1 probe cores I have shown are to figure out for orientation and how hard it is for KSP2:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EKSP1 Screenshot:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022KSP1.png?width=1202\u0026amp;height=676\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.25\u0022 height=\u0022674\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/1039965578754007060/1110380780519166012/KSP1.png?width=1202\u0026amp;height=676\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EKSP2 Screenshot:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022KSP2_Problem_Probe_Cores.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/1039965578754007060/1110380738735513640/KSP2_Problem_Probe_Cores.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ESuggestions:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EWithout changing how the probe cores look in KSP2:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nHave an indicator that shows direction and its angle on picking up the probe core/craft (If it\u0027s going to be upside down for example for a rover)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nAnother way might be to have something similar to the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECOL\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Thrust\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Thrust\u0022\u003ECOT\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E buttons to turn the orientation indicators off and on.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-06-02T00:22:30Z\u0022 title=\u002206/02/2023 12:22  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EJune 2, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Anth12\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}